    <h2 style="margin-top: 0;">⚖️ Legal Framework: Documented Crimes</h2>

    <h3>Applicability of International Humanitarian Law</h3>
    <p><strong>Geneva Conventions (I-IV):</strong> Protection of civilians, wounded, prisoners, healthcare facilities. All attacks on schools, hospitals, civilian infrastructure violate Conventions.</p>

    <p><strong>Additional Protocols (I-II):</strong> Prohibition of indiscriminate attacks, weapons of particularly cruel nature (cluster munitions, white phosphorus in civilian areas), cultural property protection.</p>

    <p><strong>ICC Statute (Rome):</strong> Article 8 defines war crimes:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Deliberate attack on civilians:</strong> Schools, hospitals, civilian infrastructure without legitimate military purpose</li>
      <li><strong>Indiscriminate attacks:</strong> Bombardments not distinguishing civilians from combatants</li>
      <li><strong>Prohibited weapons:</strong> White phosphorus in inhabited areas, cluster munitions in civilian zones</li>
      <li><strong>Massacre: >150 civilians killed in single incident (Minab meets criteria)</strong></li>
      <li><strong>Crimes Against Humanity:</strong> Murder, persecution, extermination (denying education to 658,000 children)</li>
    </ul>

